    base:desc "The Digital Twin system is orchestrated according to the Digital Shadow Reference Model (Fig. 1). The model defines a class diagram that connects DataTrace objects with their originating Source, the associated Model (engineering, simulation, or data‑calculation), and a Processing component that consumes input traces and produces output traces. Concrete realization of the reference model involves mapping each reference concept to concrete elements, thereby incarnating the abstract architecture. The Processing component encodes the execution logic of the linked models and provides fine‑grained traceability via the ‘originates‑from’ association, which enables transitive tracing of data lineage throughout the twin. This arrangement constitutes the overall coordination and resource management pattern for the Digital Twin."
]

